  "grain": "one row per client process/task delivered by EXL — a Function (L1) > Function (L2) > Process (L3) > Task at a specific EXL delivery location — with its staffing, volumes, SLAs, pricing, and transformation notes",
  "row_count": 811,
  "summary": "The main operational inventory of the workbook: each row is a discrete process or task that EXL runs for a named insurance client at a given delivery location. Columns capture the client and its geography, the EXL delivery site/country and process manager, a four-level process taxonomy (Function L1/L2, Process L3, Task) with a free-text description, business line / line-of-business, staffing counts (billable FTEs, SME/QA/trainer, supervisors, buffer roster, total staff), volumes and handling time, SLAs and quality methodology, pain points, and implemented/planned digital solutions with their expected benefits. It answers who EXL serves, what work is done where, how it is staffed and priced, and what transformation is underway.",
  "use_cases": [
    "What processes or tasks does EXL run for a given client (e.g. Nationwide)?",
    "Total Staff or Billable FTEs by client, function, or EXL delivery location (aggregation/ranking)",
    "Which delivery countries/sites handle Claims vs Underwriting vs Sales & Service work? (segment/filter)",
    "What is the pricing model and annual rate for a client's processes?",
    "Which processes have digital solutions implemented or planned, and what benefits are expected? (filter)",
    "Average monthly volume, AHT, and SLAs for a specific process or task (lookup)"
  ],
